looks at you growing up in the
'90s, almost out of the '90s,

00:10:54.220 --> 00:10:55.750 align:middle line:10%
wanting to change the world.

00:10:55.750 --> 00:10:58.990 align:middle line:84%
And they think we're just
those woo woo people.

00:10:58.990 --> 00:11:02.140 align:middle line:84%
They think we're just sort
of those do-gooder people.

00:11:02.140 --> 00:11:05.140 align:middle line:84%
I think it's time to talk
about practical advice.

00:11:05.140 --> 00:11:09.250 align:middle line:84%
And I love that
you have a concept

00:11:09.250 --> 00:11:11.710 align:middle line:84%
of putting practical
advice out there

00:11:11.710 --> 00:11:13.930 align:middle line:84%
in the world for
people your age.

00:11:13.930 --> 00:11:15.200 align:middle line:90%
So let's talk about that.

00:11:15.200 --> 00:11:17.620 align:middle line:90%
What is some of that advice?

00:11:17.620 --> 00:11:21.280 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean, it's just really
so basically just comes down

00:11:21.280 --> 00:11:22.720 align:middle line:90%
to like, what's life about?

00:11:22.720 --> 00:11:23.740 align:middle line:90%
What's human?

00:11:23.740 --> 00:11:24.970 align:middle line:84%
>> But that's what I
want to hear about.

00:11:24.970 --> 00:11:25.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Like what's the point?

00:11:25.570 --> 00:11:26.320 align:middle line:90%
Like why are we here?

00:11:26.320 --> 00:11:27.140 align:middle line:90%
What's the point?

00:11:27.140 --> 00:11:28.748 align:middle line:90%
I thought it's really clear.

00:11:28.748 --> 00:11:30.040 align:middle line:90%
It's like it's about happiness.

00:11:30.040 --> 00:11:30.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:11:30.450 --> 00:11:31.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Right?

00:11:31.250 --> 00:11:32.200 align:middle line:90%
And it's everybody.

00:11:32.200 --> 00:11:33.770 align:middle line:84%
Universally, we all
want to be happy.

00:11:33.770 --> 00:11:34.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:11:34.570 --> 00:11:36.028 align:middle line:10%
>> And so how do
we find happiness?

00:11:36.028 --> 00:11:38.600 align:middle line:10%
I mean, do we find
happiness in judgment,

00:11:38.600 --> 00:11:40.660 align:middle line:10%
or do we find happiness
in forgiveness?

00:11:40.660 --> 00:11:42.250 align:middle line:84%
And do we find
happiness in anger,

00:11:42.250 --> 00:11:43.670 align:middle line:90%
or do we find happiness in love?

00:11:43.670 --> 00:11:44.470 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:11:44.470 --> 00:11:45.910 align:middle line:90%
So I mean, it's practical.

00:11:45.910 --> 00:11:46.780 align:middle line:90%
It's really basic.

00:11:46.780 --> 00:11:48.010 align:middle line:90%
It's not woo woo.

00:11:48.010 --> 00:11:50.020 align:middle line:90%
It's not anything.

00:11:50.020 --> 00:11:50.930 align:middle line:90%
It's just what is.

00:11:50.930 --> 00:11:51.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:11:51.730 --> 00:11:52.530 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:11:52.530 --> 00:11:56.770 align:middle line:84%
>> And it's just about utilizing
practices that encourage love,

00:11:56.770 --> 00:12:01.360 align:middle line:84%
that encourage forgiveness,
that encourage awakening,

00:12:01.360 --> 00:12:03.700 align:middle line:84%
whatever you want to
call it, consciousness,

00:12:03.700 --> 00:12:06.887 align:middle line:84%
awareness of who we are
and what we're doing here.

00:12:06.887 --> 00:12:08.470 align:middle line:84%
And that, yeah, we
all want happiness.

00:12:08.470 --> 00:12:10.012 align:middle line:84%
And some of us think
that we're going

00:12:10.012 --> 00:12:13.600 align:middle line:84%
to find happiness by beating
each other, by revenge,

00:12:13.600 --> 00:12:14.590 align:middle line:90%
by those things.

00:12:14.590 --> 00:12:16.300 align:middle line:84%
Just switching that
and seeing clearly

00:12:16.300 --> 00:12:18.970 align:middle line:84%
that that never has brought
happiness to anybody

00:12:18.970 --> 00:12:22.150 align:middle line:84%
and it never will, and that
will bring happiness to you

00:12:22.150 --> 00:12:26.200 align:middle line:84%
is forgiving yourself
and forgiving that person

00:12:26.200 --> 00:12:29.050 align:middle line:84%
and learning to love
better and learning

00:12:29.050 --> 00:12:31.720 align:middle line:90%
to be more peaceful and happy.

00:12:31.720 --> 00:12:34.090 align:middle line:84%
And so yeah, it's
very practical.

00:12:34.090 --> 00:12:37.840 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's almost silly
to even call it practical.

00:12:37.840 --> 00:12:40.580 align:middle line:84%
It's just it's
such common sense.

00:12:40.580 --> 00:12:44.590 align:middle line:84%
But for some reason, we've
gotten so far away from that,

00:12:44.590 --> 00:12:49.420 align:middle line:84%
that now it seems woo woo or
seems like some hippie ideal

00:12:49.420 --> 00:12:51.335 align:middle line:90%
to be happy, to be peaceful.

00:12:51.335 --> 00:12:53.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you see the importance
of talking about it, though?

00:12:53.710 --> 00:12:54.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Of course.

00:12:54.070 --> 00:12:56.260 align:middle line:84%
>> There are people, I
believe, who are hungry

00:12:56.260 --> 00:12:57.600 align:middle line:90%
for the knowledge.

00:12:57.600 --> 00:13:00.790 align:middle line:84%
And though it is just
practical and basic,

00:13:00.790 --> 00:13:03.830 align:middle line:84%
I think it's important to
still put it out there and say,

00:13:03.830 --> 00:13:05.350 align:middle line:90%
this is how you begin.

00:13:05.350 --> 00:13:09.760 align:middle line:84%
There's a huge wave of
spirituality crossing America

00:13:09.760 --> 00:13:12.440 align:middle line:84%
in terms of health and
the environment, Ocean,

00:13:12.440 --> 00:13:15.700 align:middle line:84%
what practical advice
do you put out there?

00:13:15.700 --> 00:13:18.460 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, a lot of people
feel overwhelmed by the state

00:13:18.460 --> 00:13:19.510 align:middle line:10%
of our world today.

00:13:19.510 --> 00:13:22.000 align:middle line:10%
And a lot of people feel
like their only options

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:26.770 align:middle line:10%
are to be lost in despair or
to go numb and push it away.

00:13:26.770 --> 00:13:29.740 align:middle line:10%
I think we have a third option,
which is far more appealing.

00:13:29.740 --> 00:13:32.390 align:middle line:84%
And that's to seek to
find a positive response.

00:13:32.390 --> 00:13:36.580 align:middle line:84%
I think that we can hear
the problems around us

00:13:36.580 --> 00:13:39.920 align:middle line:84%
as a call to a place
inside us that says, hey,

00:13:39.920 --> 00:13:42.280 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to just stand
by and let this go on.

00:13:42.280 --> 00:13:44.390 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to do
something about it.

00:13:44.390 --> 00:13:46.090 align:middle line:84%
The bigger the
problems are, the more

00:13:46.090 --> 00:13:47.390 align:middle line:90%
needed we are in this world.

00:13:47.390 --> 00:13:48.190 align:middle line:90%
>> Example.

00:13:48.190 --> 00:13:51.420 align:middle line:84%
>> And for example, we can
eat lower on the food chain.

00:13:51.420 --> 00:13:54.400 align:middle line:84%
It takes 16 pounds of grain
to produce one pound of beef

00:13:54.400 --> 00:13:55.550 align:middle line:90%
in this country.

00:13:55.550 --> 00:13:57.640 align:middle line:84%
So if we eat one
less pound of beef,

00:13:57.640 --> 00:14:00.250 align:middle line:84%
we are essentially
enabling 15 people

00:14:00.250 --> 00:14:02.740 align:middle line:84%
to eat with the
food that's saved.

00:14:02.740 --> 00:14:04.250 align:middle line:90%
We can choose to recycle.

00:14:04.250 --> 00:14:07.540 align:middle line:84%
Recycling one aluminum can
saves enough energy to power

00:14:07.540 --> 00:14:09.430 align:middle line:84%
a car on the freeway
for two miles.

00:14:09.430 --> 00:14:10.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Does it really?

00:14:10.390 --> 00:14:12.265 align:middle line:84%
>> If the car gets 40
miles per gallon, yeah.

00:14:12.265 --> 00:14:13.065 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:14:13.065 --> 00:14:14.120 align:middle line:90%
That's astonishing.

00:14:14.120 --> 00:14:16.453 align:middle line:84%
>> There are huge numbers
of things we can do.

00:14:16.453 --> 00:14:18.370 align:middle line:84%
And we've just got to
start thinking about it.

00:14:18.370 --> 00:14:20.108 align:middle line:90%
Every dollar we spend is a vote.

00:14:20.108 --> 00:14:22.400 align:middle line:84%
And we're voting for the
company that made the product,

00:14:22.400 --> 00:14:24.150 align:middle line:84%
and we're voting for
the way they made it.

00:14:24.150 --> 00:14:26.453 align:middle line:84%
So do we want to support
child labor in China?

00:14:26.453 --> 00:14:28.870 align:middle line:84%
Do we want to support pesticide
deaths on the grape fields

00:14:28.870 --> 00:14:29.890 align:middle line:90%
of California?

00:14:29.890 --> 00:14:30.970 align:middle line:90%
Do we want to go organic?

00:14:30.970 --> 00:14:32.740 align:middle line:84%
Do we want to buy
from local companies?

00:14:32.740 --> 00:14:35.110 align:middle line:84%
Do we want to choose
to make our dollars

00:14:35.110 --> 00:14:37.480 align:middle line:84%
into a vote for the kind
of world we want to create?

00:14:37.480 --> 00:14:39.370 align:middle line:90%
I personally do.

00:14:39.370 --> 00:14:42.190 align:middle line:84%
>> You have me very
enrolled, Ocean.

00:14:42.190 --> 00:14:45.273 align:middle line:84%
Mr. Chopra, your personal,
practical advice?

00:14:45.273 --> 00:14:47.440 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, I think the
most practical application,

00:14:47.440 --> 00:14:49.950 align:middle line:84%
we talk about street
spirituality, I guess,

00:14:49.950 --> 00:14:50.950 align:middle line:90%
our generation.

00:14:50.950 --> 00:14:51.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:14:51.750 --> 00:14:53.590 align:middle line:10%
>> The most practical
application is, one,

00:14:53.590 --> 00:14:58.030 align:middle line:10%
to start asking the
appropriate questions.

00:14:58.030 --> 00:15:01.930 align:middle line:10%
And for young people, those are
the most fundamental things.

00:15:01.930 --> 00:15:02.780 align:middle line:90%
Why am I here?

00:15:02.780 --> 00:15:04.670 align:middle line:90%
What do I believe in?

00:15:04.670 --> 00:15:10.690 align:middle line:84%
And two, things that we can do
is the willingness to listen,

00:15:10.690 --> 00:15:14.570 align:middle line:84%
because that's the
biggest problem, I think,

00:15:14.570 --> 00:15:16.510 align:middle line:84%
is that there's
not this space yet

00:15:16.510 --> 00:15:21.190 align:middle line:84%
where young people feel secure
and safe to ask those questions

00:15:21.190 --> 00:15:23.000 align:middle line:90%
and have people listen to them.

00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:26.230 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's some
of the work we're doing

00:15:26.230 --> 00:15:28.390 align:middle line:84%
is trying to create
that space and trying

00:15:28.390 --> 00:15:31.490 align:middle line:84%
to create that vocabulary,
one, where young people can

00:15:31.490 --> 00:15:34.830 align:middle line:84%
start to talk about their
spirituality and articulate it.

00:15:34.830 --> 00:15:39.050 align:middle line:84%
But also showing the willingness
to listen and not judge.

00:15:39.050 --> 00:15:41.450 align:middle line:84%
Because sometimes, when
you ask those questions,

00:15:41.450 --> 00:15:44.160 align:middle line:84%
you come up with
some wild responses,

00:15:44.160 --> 00:15:47.240 align:middle line:90%
especially from young people.

00:15:47.240 --> 00:15:49.110 align:middle line:84%
But they don't
need to be judged.

00:15:49.110 --> 00:15:50.060 align:middle line:90%
They need to be heard.

00:15:50.060 --> 00:15:51.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, very well said.

00:15:51.170 --> 00:15:53.600 align:middle line:84%
The gift of listening
is vital in our world

00:15:53.600 --> 00:15:56.690 align:middle line:84%
today, especially
to your generation.

00:15:56.690 --> 00:15:59.450 align:middle line:84%
Are you optimistic
about the future?

00:15:59.450 --> 00:16:02.180 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, you picked
the right group to ask that

00:16:02.180 --> 00:16:03.360 align:middle line:90%
question.

00:16:03.360 --> 00:16:06.200 align:middle line:84%
Because, yeah, I think we
face tremendous challenges.

00:16:06.200 --> 00:16:09.200 align:middle line:84%
And those challenges
can be intimidating

00:16:09.200 --> 00:16:11.510 align:middle line:84%
when you look at the scale
of some of the things

00:16:11.510 --> 00:16:13.070 align:middle line:90%
that we have to resolve.

00:16:13.070 --> 00:16:14.990 align:middle line:10%
But at least amongst
this group, I've

00:16:14.990 --> 00:16:18.050 align:middle line:10%
got the feeling that
there's a willingness

00:16:18.050 --> 00:16:21.440 align:middle line:10%
to take small steps,
because, ultimately, that's

00:16:21.440 --> 00:16:23.360 align:middle line:10%
where you have to start.

00:16:23.360 --> 00:16:26.370 align:middle line:10%
And I'm very optimistic.

00:16:26.370 --> 00:16:29.400 align:middle line:10%
I mean, I know, again,
I'm excited by everything

00:16:29.400 --> 00:16:30.200 align:middle line:10%
I'm doing.

00:16:30.200 --> 00:16:33.200 align:middle line:10%
And I'm excited to go
and interact with people

00:16:33.200 --> 00:16:35.030 align:middle line:10%
and to go to schools
and meet young people,

00:16:35.030 --> 00:16:37.700 align:middle line:10%
because the assumption,
a lot of times,

00:16:37.700 --> 00:16:40.880 align:middle line:10%
is that young people
don't care, that they're

00:16:40.880 --> 00:16:42.840 align:middle line:10%
distracted by other things.

00:16:42.840 --> 00:16:46.340 align:middle line:10%
But we've found that's not
true, that if you engage

00:16:46.340 --> 00:16:50.330 align:middle line:10%
young people at a very
honest and raw level,

00:16:50.330 --> 00:16:52.820 align:middle line:10%
they'll give you the
most incredible responses

00:16:52.820 --> 00:16:57.870 align:middle line:10%
and they'll show you new ways to
really create a better future.

00:16:57.870 --> 00:16:58.670 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah.

00:16:58.670 --> 00:17:00.410 align:middle line:10%
>> What about your
optimism, Ocean?

00:17:00.410 --> 00:17:04.099 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, my level of optimism
about what I see going on out

00:17:04.099 --> 00:17:06.438 align:middle line:10%
there fluctuates every day.

00:17:06.438 --> 00:17:08.730 align:middle line:10%
Some days, I think, oh, yes,
things are turning around.

00:17:08.730 --> 00:17:09.390 align:middle line:90%
It's going to be great.

00:17:09.390 --> 00:17:12.020 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes I think, oh, no,
this world is totally doomed.

00:17:12.020 --> 00:17:14.510 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think
that that's where

00:17:14.510 --> 00:17:17.160 align:middle line:84%
we need to source in for our
strength and our courage.

00:17:17.160 --> 00:17:17.960 align:middle line:90%
>> No?

00:17:17.960 --> 00:17:20.119 align:middle line:84%
>> I think we need to source
in the hopes and the dreams

00:17:20.119 --> 00:17:21.780 align:middle line:84%
and the prayers
that live inside us.

00:17:21.780 --> 00:17:22.660 align:middle line:90%
They're eternal.

00:17:22.660 --> 00:17:23.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:17:23.460 --> 00:17:25.839 align:middle line:84%
>> They never go away
unless we snuff them out.

00:17:25.839 --> 00:17:29.480 align:middle line:84%
And as long as we are
breathing and we are praying

00:17:29.480 --> 00:17:31.520 align:middle line:84%
and we are dreaming
of a better way,

00:17:31.520 --> 00:17:33.980 align:middle line:84%
we can have optimism,
if we choose to.

00:17:33.980 --> 00:17:35.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you for that reminder.

00:17:35.850 --> 00:17:36.725 align:middle line:90%
What about you, Noah?

00:17:36.725 --> 00:17:40.160 align:middle line:84%
What are your thoughts
for your children?

00:17:40.160 --> 00:17:43.350 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I don't currently
have any children.

00:17:43.350 --> 00:17:45.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, your children
of the future.

00:17:45.200 --> 00:17:48.620 align:middle line:84%
>> As far of the future, I mean,
part of me really feels like

00:17:48.620 --> 00:17:50.990 align:middle line:84%
what's really
important is right now.

00:17:50.990 --> 00:17:54.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm not even so sure
that the future exists.

00:17:54.260 --> 00:17:57.020 align:middle line:84%
The present moment is really
what we have and is really

00:17:57.020 --> 00:17:58.383 align:middle line:90%
where we can do our work.

00:17:58.383 --> 00:18:00.800 align:middle line:84%
Certainly, all of the work
that we're doing in the present

00:18:00.800 --> 00:18:06.080 align:middle line:84%
will affect what will come,
if and when that comes.

00:18:06.080 --> 00:18:08.840 align:middle line:84%
I have a great
amount of optimism

00:18:08.840 --> 00:18:12.740 align:middle line:84%
and really deep understanding
that personal freedom is

00:18:12.740 --> 00:18:16.820 align:middle line:84%
possible and is
happening for people.

00:18:16.820 --> 00:18:20.030 align:middle line:84%
Out of my own experience,
the vast array of

00:18:20.030 --> 00:18:23.450 align:middle line:84%
experiences of suffering
and of happiness and joy

00:18:23.450 --> 00:18:28.070 align:middle line:84%
that I've had in this one
short incarnation thus far,

00:18:28.070 --> 00:18:30.620 align:middle line:84%
that that will
probably continue.

00:18:30.620 --> 00:18:32.120 align:middle line:84%
But I don't feel
real comfortable

00:18:32.120 --> 00:18:36.650 align:middle line:84%
speculating on what the
future is going to be.

00:18:36.650 --> 00:18:40.970 align:middle line:84%
I have a real faith that no
matter what it is, it'll be OK.

00:18:40.970 --> 00:18:48.900 align:middle line:10%
>> What do the three of you say
to probably the largest group

00:18:48.900 --> 00:18:53.610 align:middle line:10%
of people existing in
American society today,

00:18:53.610 --> 00:18:58.260 align:middle line:10%
and that's the baby boomers,
those of us who were you

00:18:58.260 --> 00:19:00.570 align:middle line:10%
in the 60s, those of
us who were activists,

00:19:00.570 --> 00:19:02.940 align:middle line:10%
those of us who marched in
Berkeley and Washington?

00:19:02.940 --> 00:19:05.140 align:middle line:90%
I was one of those people.

00:19:05.140 --> 00:19:07.380 align:middle line:84%
What do you say to that
group of people today?

00:19:07.380 --> 00:19:08.940 align:middle line:90%
What do you say to us?

00:19:08.940 --> 00:19:13.320 align:middle line:84%
>> I want to say, thank you
for giving us the opportunity

00:19:13.320 --> 00:19:19.248 align:middle line:84%
and giving us the upbringing to
feel empowered and comfortable

00:19:19.248 --> 00:19:21.040 align:middle line:84%
with the things that
we want to talk about.

00:19:21.040 --> 00:19:23.880 align:middle line:84%
We're very grateful,
not only to our parents,

00:19:23.880 --> 00:19:26.650 align:middle line:84%
but to their
generation at large.

00:19:26.650 --> 00:19:28.550 align:middle line:90%
So that's one thing.

00:19:28.550 --> 00:19:31.090 align:middle line:84%
And the other
thing is the dream,

00:19:31.090 --> 00:19:34.380 align:middle line:84%
I guess, is still alive,
and that some people may

00:19:34.380 --> 00:19:36.480 align:middle line:84%
have forgotten
that, may have got

00:19:36.480 --> 00:19:41.090 align:middle line:84%
caught up in the drama that
is jobs and relationships

00:19:41.090 --> 00:19:43.120 align:middle line:84%
and schools and
everything like that.

00:19:43.120 --> 00:19:45.690 align:middle line:84%
But there's still
a lot of hope left.

00:19:45.690 --> 00:19:50.170 align:middle line:84%
And we welcome them back,
if that's what it takes.

00:19:50.170 --> 00:19:51.900 align:middle line:90%
But it's exciting.

00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:55.800 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's not just
that we can make a change,

00:19:55.800 --> 00:19:58.290 align:middle line:84%
but that we are together
making a change.

00:19:58.290 --> 00:20:00.300 align:middle line:84%
And it's cool to
be a part of that.

00:20:00.300 --> 00:20:05.100 align:middle line:84%
And we're excited, whether it's
the baby boomers or Generation

00:20:05.100 --> 00:20:08.020 align:middle line:84%
Y or whoever, to jump
